decks.notes: The primary focus of this Arclight Phoenix aggro deck is to quickly fill the graveyard with spells to enable the reanimation of Arclight Phoenix and generate card advantage with Treasure Cruise. With a combination of low-cost spells and card draw, the deck aims to overwhelm opponents with efficient threats while disrupting their game plan with counter magic and removal. The inclusion of cards like Hall of Storm Giants and Profit's Eidetic Memory provide additional value and power to the deck's strategy, creating a versatile and aggressive game plan that can quickly close out games.

This Rakdos Aggro deck focuses on quickly applying pressure to the opponent with efficient creatures and disruptive spells. With early game disruption like Thoughtseize and Duress, along with removal spells like Fatal Push and Go for the Throat, the deck aims to disrupt the opponent's game plan while deploying threats like Bloodtithe Harvester and Archfiend of the Dross to close out the game quickly. The deck also utilizes lands like Castle Locthwain and Den of the Bugbear for additional value and damage potential.

This deck focuses on utilizing efficient creatures and disruptive spells to apply pressure on the opponent quickly. By playing powerful cards like Elite Spellbinder and Thalia, Guardian of Thraben, the deck aims to slow down the opponent's game plan while deploying threats of its own. Collected Company allows for explosive turns by putting multiple creatures on the battlefield at instant speed. With a mix of creatures and disruption, the deck aims to overwhelm opponents with a fast and aggressive strategy centered around the Selesnya color combination.
